The paper deals with an online clustering problem, which is a fundamental problem in data structures and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the objective of minimizing disagreements and maximizing agreements between the clustering and the input, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves information theory, which is related to cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the possibility of using randomized algorithms, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
